  "description": "Fast triage dashboard for container logs stored in Loki, designed for “what is failing?” and “who is noisy?” investigations across all stacks.\n\nWorkflow: start from aggregated error-like log rate by stack and the top offending services, then drill down via variables to a specific stack/service/container. Use the raw log panel with a non-empty search string to isolate relevant lines quickly.\n\nFiltering: error severity is controlled by $error_re (default: level=(error|critical|fatal|panic)). Adjust this regex to widen/narrow the signal depending on the incident.\n\nData source: Loki (docker logs).\n\nSecurity: logs may contain sensitive operational metadata (hostnames, internal services, user identifiers, tokens in query params). Restrict dashboard access and avoid sharing raw log output without redaction.",
